Shares of Tesla Inc. TSLA, -2.72% sank 5.7% in premarket trading Thursday, extending the pullback after an epic recent rally to a record close earlier this week. After more than doubling (up 112%) year to date, including a 59% jump in six days to Tuesday's peak of $887.06, the stock tumbled 17.2% on Wednesday. A downgrade at Canaccord Genuity Wednesday helped fuel the pullback. The stock has now lost 21.9% since Tuesday's record close. Nicholas Colas, co-founder of DataTrek Research, noted that while Tesla's stock is not in the S&P 500 SPX, +0.17%, it carries a 1.9% weighting in the Nasdaq 100 NDX, +0.00%. And the Invesco QQQ ETF QQQ, +0.12%, which tracks the Nasdaq 100, owns more Tesla shares than any other ETF, at $1.5 billion worth as of Wednesday. The triple-Qs have gained 7.3% year to date, while the S&P 500 has tacked on 3.2%.
